Objective: 
The objective of this assignment is to assess your skills and knowledge as a Software Engineer in the areas 
of Python Flask/Django, MySQL, and Git concepts. You will be required to complete a series of tasks that 
simulate real-world scenarios and demonstrate your understanding and proficiency in these technologies. 

Task 2: Database Interaction 
 a. Create a MySQL database with the name "users". 
 b. Design a table "users" with the following columns: 
 - id (int, primary key) 
 - name (varchar) 
 - email (varchar) 
 - role (varchar) 
 c. Write SQL queries to: 
 - Insert sample data into the "users" table. 
 - Retrieve all users from the "users" table. 
 - Retrieve a specific user by their ID.
 
Preview:
a. For Creating database use 
CREATE DATABASE users;
b.Before creating the table we need to use the database first
USE users;
Then create table by
CREATE TABLE users(id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR (20), email VARCHAR (20),role VARCHAR (20));
C. Then insert sample demo values into the table by 
INSERT INTO users VALUES (1,'aafreen','aaf@gmail.com','web developer');
INSERT INTO users values(2,'afreen','afreen@gmail.com','web developer');
INSERT INTO users values(3,'savitha','savi@gmail.com',' application developer');
INSERT INTO users values(4,'sharmila','sharmila@gmail.com','web developer');
INSERT INTO users values(5,'afrose','afrose@gmail.com',' Accountant');

Retrieve all the user by
SELECT * FROM users;

Retrieve specific user by
SELECT * FROM users WHERE I'd=2;


